@node INTRO " Introduction. "

   @{u} iNtRo @{uu}


   Here  ya  got  some cool IMHO ARexx scripts for use with @{fg shine}DirectoryOpus 4.xx@{fg text}. All written by me,
just  to  expand  the @{fg shine}DOpus@{fg text} functions. First - they were just for me, but now I thought, that they
could be useful to you, so I decided to relase them on the @{i}Aminet@{ui}.

   Scriptz  are  totally  @{b}freeware@{ub}, so you can spread them freely. I give you also a permission to
change them - if you think, that you can do something better, but under one condition: send me yor
modified  version to my email. I'll be nice if you send me some words just to let me know that you
are using my stuff. Adresses can be found in the @{" oUtRo " LINK OUTRO} section.

   Now, let's see what we got here.

 @{b}À @{fg fill}AmigaAMP.dopus@{fg text}@{ub}
   @{u}main purpose:@{uu}
      Send MP3/MP2/MP1 music files to @{fg shine}AmigaAmp@{fg text} and play them.
   @{u}features:@{uu}
      À check if the @{fg shine}AmigaAmp@{fg text} is running (if not - run it)
      À send files into just-opened @{fg shine}AmigaAmp@{fg text}, and play first from the selection
      À add files into earlier-opened @{fg shine}AmigaAmp@{fg text} (files will be waiting for it's turn)

 @{b}À @{fg fill}AMPlifier.dopus@{fg text}@{ub}
   @{u}main purpose:@{uu}
      Send MP3/MP2/MP1 music files to @{fg shine}Amplifier@{fg text} and play them.
   @{u}features:@{uu}
      À check if the @{fg shine}Amplifier@{fg text} is running (if not - run it)
      À send files into just-opened @{fg shine}Amplifier@{fg text}, and play first from the selection
      À add files into earlier-opened @{fg shine}Amplifier@{fg text} (files will be waiting for it's turn)

 @{b}À @{fg fill}PictureInfo.dopus@{fg text}@{ub}
   @{u}main purpose:@{uu}
      Show some infos about graphic files (may be handy for html writers).
   @{u}features:@{uu}
      À support for BMP, GIF, IFF, JPEG, PBM, PCX, PNG, PSD, SUN, TARGA and TIFF files
      À shows size (width x height) of the picture
      À shows file format (GIF, IFF etc.)

 @{b}À @{fg fill}SmartCopy.dopus@{fg text}@{ub}
   @{u}main purpose:@{uu}
      Copy files from one place to another.
   @{u}features:@{uu}
      À check if the selected files are in the active window
      À if yes, just copy them
      À if not, ask if it is required to swap windows, and if it is, copy the files

 @{b}À @{fg fill}SmartMove.dopus@{fg text}@{ub}
   @{u}main purpose:@{uu}
      Move files from one place to another.
   @{u}features:@{uu}
      À same as above, but don't copy - just move :-)

 @{b}À @{fg fill}WhatSize.dopus@{fg text}@{ub}
   @{u}main purpose:@{uu}
      Get size of all selected files and directories.
   @{u}features:@{uu}
      À get size of all files and directories
      À check if they all will fit into place listed in other window
      À display size in few formats at one time (bytes, Kilobytes, Megabytes, Gigabytes)
      À check  how  many disks (Amiga OFS, Amiga FFS, PC DD) is required to store all the selected
        stuff
      À check how many CD-ROMs (200Mb, 650Mb, 700Mb) is required to store all the selected stuff
      À it displays the Gb size only if selection is bigger than 500 Mb
      À it displays the CD-R number only if selection is bigger than the 10% of CD's capacity

   All of them use the @{fg shine}DOpus@{fg text}-rendered GUI.


   This relase is dedicated to some personal friends of mine.

@endnode

@node REQUI " Requirements. "

   @{u} rEQUiREMENts @{uu}


   It's  now  very fashionable to make something that needs a small rocket, not a simple computer.
My  scripts are very small, but it doesn't mean that they need a small monster. All you need is an
@{b}Amiga@{ub} compatible  computer  -  probably  also  the @{b}UAE@{ub}. Hard disk is nice, but not required. Hmmm,
all  you need is a machine, where you can run @{fg shine}Directory Opus 4.xx@{fg text}, and @{fg shine}ARexx@{fg text}. If you wanna use the
@{fg fill}AmigaAMP.dopus@{fg text}  script  -  you'll need @{fg shine}AmigaAmp@{fg text} (check it for the requirements), and with the file
@{fg fill}PictureInfo.dopus@{fg text}  you  must  have  the  @{fg shine}GetImageInfo@{fg text} (by @{i}Christian Effenberger@{ui}) command in the @{u}C:@{uu}
directory. All of these can be found on the @{i}Aminet@{ui} ofcourse.

   Scripts were tested on my machine, and works fine (with one exception - see @{" bUGz " LINK BUGZY}):

 @{b}À@{ub} Amiga 1240/25Mhz with PPC603e/175Mhz
 @{b}À@{ub} 32 Mb Fast RAM
 @{b}À@{ub} 2.1Gb + 340Mb WDCaviar HardDisks
 @{b}À@{ub} Samsung CD x32
 @{b}À@{ub} 15" SVGA monitor (used with ScanDoubler)

   with soft:

 @{b}À@{ub} @{fg shine}DirectoryOpus@{fg text} v4.16
 @{b}À@{ub} @{fg shine}RexxMast@{fg text} v36.5
 @{b}À@{ub} @{fg shine}AmigaAmp@{fg text} v2.9▀1
 @{b}À@{ub} @{fg shine}Amplifier@{fg text} v2.10
 @{b}À@{ub} @{fg shine}GetImageInfo@{fg text} v1.0

@endnode

@node INSTA " Installation. "

   @{u} iNStAllAtiOn @{uu}


   Is  quite  simply.  All you need is copy the files to the place, where you keep the @{fg shine}DOpus@{fg text} ARexx
scripts. I've got it in my @{u}REXX:DOPUS@{uu} directory.
   Documentation (this file) you can copy wherever you want.
   After that, you must configure @{fg shine}DOpus@{fg text}. My sample config is in the next chapter - @{" uSAGe " LINK USAGE}.

@endnode

@node USAGE " Usage. "

   @{u} uSAGe @{uu}

   Here is my @{fg shine}DOpus@{fg text} configuration for the scripts.

 @{b}À @{fg fill}AmigaAMP.dopus@{fg text}@{ub}
   @{u}section:@{uu} filetypes,  setting  for  the  MPx  files (the file recognition thing you must make by
      yourself).
   @{u}events:@{uu} @{i}action Double-Click@{ui} and @{i}Command play@{ui}
   @{u}command:@{uu} <AmigaDOS> RX REXX:DOPUS/AmigaAMP.dopus {F}
   @{u}flags:@{uu} No filename quote
          Run asynchronously
   @{u}stack:@{uu} 200000
   @{u}close:@{uu} 2
   (you also must change the @{b}AMPExe@{ub} string to your path to @{fg shine}AmigaAmp@{fg text} executable)

      or if you are using @{fg shine}Amplifier@{fg text}:

 @{b}À @{fg fill}AMPlifier.dopus@{fg text}@{ub}
   @{u}section:@{uu} filetypes,  setting  for  the  MPx  files (the file recognition thing you must make by
      yourself).
   @{u}events:@{uu} @{i}action Double-Click@{ui} and @{i}Command play@{ui}
   @{u}command:@{uu} <ARexx> REXX:DOPUS/AMPlifier.dopus
   @{u}stack:@{uu} 200000
   @{u}close:@{uu} 2
   (you also must change the @{b}AMPExe@{ub} string to your path to @{fg shine}Amplifier@{fg text} executable)

 @{b}À @{fg fill}PictureInfo.dopus@{fg text}@{ub}
   @{u}section:@{uu} buttons (name, colour and location is free :-)
   @{u}command:@{uu} <ARexx> REXX:DOPUS/PictureInfo.dopus
   @{u}flags:@{uu} CD Source
          No filename quote
          Run asynchronously
   @{u}stack:@{uu} 64000
   @{u}close:@{uu} 2

 @{b}À @{fg fill}SmartCopy.dopus@{fg text}@{ub}
   @{u}section:@{uu} buttons (name, colour and location is free :-)
   @{u}command:@{uu} <ARexx> REXX:DOPUS/SmartCopy.dopus

 @{b}À @{fg fill}SmartMove.dopus@{fg text}@{ub}
   @{u}section:@{uu} buttons (name, colour and location is free :-)
   @{u}command:@{uu} <ARexx> REXX:DOPUS/SmartMove.dopus

 @{b}À @{fg fill}WhatSize.dopus@{fg text}@{ub}
   @{u}section:@{uu} buttons (name, colour and location is free :-)
   @{u}command:@{uu} <ARexx> REXX:DOPUS/WhatSize.dopus

   Ofcourse you must change the string @{u}REXX:DOPUS/@{uu} into your path to the files!
@endnode

@node BUGZY " Bugz. "

   @{u} bUGz @{uu}


   Rite now I know only one bug for the @{fg fill}WhatSize.dopus@{fg text} script.
   It's  probably  caused by @{fg shine}DOpus@{fg text} itself, or the Amiga File System. Well, when one of the windows
lists  the  PC  partitions/disks greater than 2Gb (I guess), @{fg shine}DOpus@{fg text} (and the script) hangs. All you
can  do is to reboot the Amiga. I don't know if it will show up at your computer. I saw this error
when  I  connected  my friend's 4Gb hard disk, formatted under Win98. I mounted it with @{b}Fat95@{ub} file
system  in  @{u}L:@{uu},  I  wanted  to  copy  some mp3s into this disk, I clicked on the button @{fg background}@{bg text}What Size?@{fg text}@{bg background}
(button  that  runs my script), and my Amiga hung. The info window was displayed, but with strange
numbers instead of sizes. By now, I dunno how to fix it.

@endnode

